After serializing the very successful Slam Dunk in Weekly Shonen Jump, Takehiko Inoue created a second basketball-themed manga but this one was first released online, unedited with even the text drawn by Takehiko. After its release, it was picked up by Shueisha (the publisher his previous works had been with) and serialized in Monthly Shonen Jump before being printed in four volumes. It has been translated to Korean, Chinese and English.

description:
Combining the classic novel, The Wonderful Wizard of Oz, and its sequel, The Marvelous Land of Oz, into one lavishly-illustrated edition, readers will be able to re-experience the original story that spawned numerous popular plays, television shows, and films. The work will feature lovely manga-inspired illustrations by artist Kriss Sison, who previously illustrated an omnibus edition of Alice‚Äôs Adventures in Wonderland and Through the Looking-Glass.

Follow young Dorothy Gale as she is whisked away to the strange and magical world of Oz. There she meets a host of endearing and colorful characters, such as the Scarecrow, the Tin Man, and the Cowardly Lion. Dorothy and her new-found friends will embark on a grand adventure to seek out the mysterious Wizard of Oz who can grant any wish, and thwart the Wicked Witch of the West. Then readers will meet young Tip, a boy from Oz who has been victimized by the wicked witch known as Mombi. Can Tip defeat the witch, against impossible odds, and discover his true destiny?
name: The Wonderful Wizard of Oz & The Marvelous Land of Oz
